Visited the truck today in loves park. Friendly staff and the steak taco I got was amazing! Im happy to pay a little more for the flavor and experience.

First time ordering from Cantina taco and I got the 10 pack take home tacos.  It was extra for pork instead of chicken but ok.  Was extra for jalapeños and extra cheese but not to bad.  Total was about 3.30 per taco.  Now on to quality the pork was cold (which it is supposed to be for take home pack) but when I say it was juicy enough to throw in a skillet and cook up without getting super dry and rubbery i mean it excellently done.  Next the toppings, all the toppings were super fresh and well portioned for the amount of tacos recieved.  Would have liked a little more meat based on how we dished them up but who wouldn't.  Don't let the sauce trick you, you'd think the green is mild and you'd be wrong.  Queso was to die for. The mild salsa was just their taco sauce so a little disappointed there.  Overall I was looking for fresh tacos to hit a spot and they did the trick fantastically.  Well worth a try!  I will be back soon.
Great tacos. The staff was very helpful and very energetic to pour a growler.
The food was absolutely delicious it had great flavor and they were very quick to get it out to me. So I will definitely be coming back
The best food I've had in a long time. Pleasant taste, made to perfection.  Staff was warm friendly, and professional. I will be returning, and telling all my friends.
Was pleasantly surprised .  Tacos were amazing.  Stopped in for lunch,  debating going back to get more for dinner .  Well done 👏👏 👏
They have the best tacos ever. They nachos is the bomb. Quality of service with the best seasoning on every bite.
Whoever the guy is who works the front is super rude and shouldn’t work with the customers he should Be a dishwasher food was great but the service was awful
Good tacos, and taste great, but quite expensive. We all know Hispanic dishes are on the lower end for cost to make. We are not in Portland people, $11 for 3 tacos is quite ridiculous.

Delicious hole-in-the-wall taco joint. Tacos, salsa, and chips are fantastic. Not the cheapest or most traditional, but a solid lunch option!

Tacos to die for. Tortillas were warm, salsa was fresh, and my soyrizo was so tasty. My family loves the meat options but for vegetarians, I highly recommend this place as well.  Also can’t forget to mention they offer local beers.
Never heard of it, tried it, wayyyyyyyy better than Chipotle’s! Got a new favorite!
Super delicious, quick and affordable. Convenient for downtown workers.

My boss offered up the opportunity to have birthday burritos for our team for our meal for our special day... I hadn’t tried this place yet so I asked to try Cantina for my treat for the staff.  This place has all the fixings for a delicious meal... it’s like a local chipotle but better.  All the burritos were amazing.  The one staff member who ordered tacos wasn’t all that pleased.  They make it easy for vegans and carnivores alike to have all their flavor delights met.  I’m definitely a fan. Love at first bite.  Thank you for the delicious birthday meal.  It definitely added to my RAD day.

Screw City taco is the only thing I’d recommend eating from here. My shrimp taco was weak and hardly had any shrimp. Ordered sour cream as well and you couldn’t even taste or see it on there barely. Save your money and drive another mile up the street. Inside Chiquita Grocery store is a Mexican restaurant that doesn’t  skimp on toppings or actual meat Inside the taco. My total was 10 and change for 2 tacos and a fountain drink. I’m still hungry. I’d expect to be full spending that much on lunch. I won’t be back.

I would try this place again and try something different!  It was also convenient for anyone who works downtown.

Cantina taco is sooooo goooood! They have a good variety of traditional tacos along with some interesting variations like the indian curry taco or the spicy thai taco. The burrito bowls are a nice healthy and tasty option, or the nachos if you're looking for a heavier lunch. Good selection of salsas and sauces, I prefer the mango habanero for a nice sweet and spicy mix. The owner and staff are very friendly.
I love the chicken tacos, get it atleast once a week during lunch!
Absolutely the best tacos I've had in Rockford! I strongly recommend the curry and chorizo varieties.
I got the chicken burrito bowl and can't wait to come back and have it again! Fantastic!
Perfect for a quick bite on a lunch break. Lots of different options to customize your taco or burrito (important for a picky eater like me).

The quality was over all very well and the taste was great however they are a bit pricey. The staff could be a little more engaged and greet you with a smile especially around busy times I know the servers are being pulled in a million different directions but a little smile can go a long way
I can't really give a fully honest review because the only thing I ever get is the cantina tacos. They're really really good. I've heard the cantina bowls are pretty good too.
Love this place! The taco bowls are my favorite, love the curry chicken.

I gave this 5 stars previously and now I drop it down to 2 stars because the portion size is half what it used to be but the price is the same.  The last few times I've ordered within the past few months there is less and less and less.  The container on today's order (5/1/2019) was maybe half full.  Sometimes I pay for extras in my burrito bowl and I never get it.  DON'T pay for extra.  Most of the time there is hardly any rice.  When I mark that I want Jalapeno's, I want Jalapeno's!!  Not just 4 of 5 slices...Come on!  I used to have a Jalapeno for nearly every bite.  The typical total is nearly $13.00 for delivery (not including the tip) on a burrito bowl without extras.  That is very expensive for what you get.  This is very disappointing because it really is good.  The portions used to be much better.  I hope your experience is more positive than mine.  What happened  to the portions Cantina Taco?

Excellent food. Fresh, colorful, flavorful, great price point, nice staff. What more can you ask for. I got the bowl and my husband got the nachos. I like that you can pick as many toppings as you want and most (90%) of them are no additional charge. Also they offered vegan meat options which was AWESOME! Thanks for not forgetting about a huge market that often either gets overlooked or price gouged. 👍👍 Two thumbs up!
